io.spine.base

Interface EntityState<I>

  • Type Parameters:
    I - the type of entity identifiers
    All Superinterfaces:
    KnownMessage, com.google.protobuf.Message, com.google.protobuf.MessageLite, com.google.protobuf.MessageLiteOrBuilder, com.google.protobuf.MessageOrBuilder, java.io.Serializable, SerializableMessage

    @Immutable
 @GeneratedMixin
public interface EntityState<I>
extends KnownMessage
    A common interface for entity state messages.

    Any message that defines an (entity) option with a valid kind is marked with this interface by the Model Compiler.

    The first field of the entity state message is treated as its identifier. It is a convention that has two goals:

    1. The definition of an entity state always starts with its ID with no extra Protobuf options. This way it's feels easy and more natural to read the code.
    2. Developers don't forget to specify which of the fields declared in Protobuf corresponds to the entity ID.

    At codegen-time, the Model Compiler substitutes the generic parameter <I> with an actual type of the first field of the entity state message.
